.\" Manpage for local-domains.
.\" Contact office@djordjejocic.com to correct errors or typos.
.TH LOCAL-DOMAINS "1" "23 Nov 2018" "1.1.3" "General Commands Manual"
.SH NAME
local-domains \- manages domains on Debian and Debian-based distributions.
.SH SYNOPSIS
local-domains [mode] [options|flags]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Local Domains is a simple BASH script for creating local domains on Debian and Debian-based distributions.
.SH OPTIONS
Adds a local domain and restarts apache.

.I Available modes:
.TP
\fB -a\fR, \fB-\-add\fR
Select add mode.
.TP
\fB -r\fR, \fB-\-remove\fR
Select remove mode.
.TP
\fB -i\fR, \fB-\-interactive\fR
.TP
.I Available options:
.TP
\fB -d\fR, \fB-\-domain\fR
Domain that needs to be added or removed.
.TP
\fB -e\fR, \fB-\-ip-address\fR
IP address that should be assigned to the domains.
.TP
\fB -o\fR, \fB-\-root-dir\fR
Root directory of a domain.
.TP
\fB -m\fR, \fB-\-server-admin\fR
Server admin's email address.
.TP
\fB -f\fR, \fB-\-cert-file\fR
Certificate file location.
.TP
\fB -k\fR, \fB-\-cert-key\fR
Certificate key location.
.TP
\fB -l\fR, \fB-\-list\fR
Lists all available domains.
.TP
\fB -h\fR, \fB-\-help\fR
Display this help and exit.
.TP
\fB-\-install\fR
Install required dependencies automatically.
.TP
\fB-\-version\fR
Output version information and exit.
.TP
.I Available flags:
.TP
\fB -p\fR, \fB-\-purge\fR
Purges root directory of a domain.
.TP
\fB -s\fR, \fB-\-ssl\fR
Enable SSL.
.TP
\fB -v\fR, \fB-\-verbose\fR
Explain what is being done.
.SH SEE ALSO
Full documentation is also available at: <http://www.github.com/jocic/BASH.LocalDomains>

apache2(1)
.SH BUGS
There are no known bugs.
.SH AUTHOR
Đorđe Jocić (office@djordjejocic.com)
